   Release Notes:

   Raycatcher is an innovative new game that syncs gameplay to your         
   favorite mp3s. Load in your entire music library and watch as the game   
   morphs itself to match. The gameplay itself is easy to pick up, yet      
   compelling. Rotate a cluster of colorful shapes to catch matching rays   
   of light cast onto your screen. As you match light to shape, your        
   cluster will expand and evolve.                                          
                                                                            
   Raycatcher also comes with a selection of great music from the           
   brilliant new artist Noobie Noobinson.                                   
                                                                            
   Load in your own music: Raycatcher will accept .mp3 and .wav formats     
                                                                            
   Beat detection technology: Changes gameplay to match your music in       
   pleasant and creative ways                                               
                                                                            
   Make playlists of any length: Raycatcher is flexible and allows you to   
   play for how ever long you want, and still feel like you've made         
   progress                                                                 
                                                                            
   Original music by artist Noobie Noobinson: Music by a new up and         
   coming band, some of which was created specifically for Raycatcher       
                                                                            
   30 evolutionary stages: Complete with funny and enlightening             
   descriptions. Raycatcher illustrates a cute and informative view of      
   the kosmos                                                               
                                                                            
   Range of difficulty: Easy to pick up, with 3 difficulty levels that      
   range from easy-yet-challenging to insanely difficult
